        7/25/2011
    

What a sale!  The fifty-percent-off signs are everywhere at this store!  Unfortunately this meant that one of the shirt styles that my friend had her eye on  --  a tissue-thin white long-sleeved collar shirt with a good true-blue flower motif (very summer-y, yet it could be worn with a blazer, to dress it up a bit)  --  was disappearing, only two left!  I myself have two things on my aeropostale wish list:  one of their light, breezey colognes, and the pure-white, cotton aeropostale bag (completely washable) that is perfect for shopping or for a binder and school-work (for all you collegiates).  Ifirst learned about aeropostale because I am friends with Great Mall Guru.  The Guru is a fashion-blogger who keeps up with fashion everything.  The Guru especially likes the Great Mall shopping community.  One more thing  --  the Guru has a good heart and really good fashion taste  --  nothing dark, but instead light, and uncomplicated.  Here's the Guru's address, just in case you want to visit:  greatmallguru.blogspot.c…   Go aeropostale!  Go surfers!  and Go Guru!!!




